I'm not sure how to  accomplish this but here goes:<br>
<br>
Find someway to make it so that 'the regulars' don't jam things down our throats everytime a new person brings up an idea. I can't count the times I have seen someone newish comment on wizards and have 'the regulars' go with the 'this is old, why talk about it' routine.<br>
<br>
While I'm at it, I'd like to see alot less negativity towards other posters in the EQ general and OT forums. I'd like to see the real negativity only allowed in rants. <br>
<br>
I guess that would mean stricter moderation and enforcement (private message warnings maybe?) which I would be for. <br>
<br>
I do know that the political discussions in OT made me stop reading for a long while.<br>
<br>
thanks, <br>
